<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A chicken has laid an enormous egg that could be Britain's biggest ever - and even had another egg inside.</p>

<p>Debbie James, from Bridgend, South Wales, bought chickens during lockdown and one had laid a huge egg.</p>

<p>The nine-month-old chicken, named Jax, tends to lay larger eggs than the rest but they think this one may be the largest in the UK.   </p>

<p>Debbie James, from Bridgend, South Wales, bought chickens during lockdown and one had laid a huge egg almost four inches tall </p>

<p>The egg measured over eight inches in circumference and was almost four inches tall. </p>

<p>When the egg was cracked open there was even another one inside, making it extra special. </p>

<p>Jax eats a lot of vegetables and loves cabbage, as well as eating her normal food.  </p>

<p>When the egg measured over eight inches and when it was cracked open there was even another one inside, making it extra special</p>

<p>The nine-month-old chicken, named Jax, pictured, tends to lay larger eggs than the rest but they think this one may be the largest in the UK</p>

<p>The previous biggest in the UK was believed to be nearly eight inches in circumference and weighed 200 grams.   </p>

<p>Ms James used the egg to make custard and meringue as she wanted to do 'something special' with it.</p>

<p>Although she said it 'tasted just the same as normal' it still felt special due to the large size of the egg.   </p>

